claim.claim-text:
1. A computer-implemented method for conducting wagering games on a wagering game system, the wagering game system including one or more input devices, one or more display devices, and one or more processors, the method comprising:
initially awarding, via at least one of the one or more processors, a plurality of plays N of the wagering game and a predetermined number of positional game modifiers X, the plurality of plays N including play N1 and play N2 and the predetermined number of positional game modifiers X including modifier X1 and modifier X2, each play of the plurality of plays N including a set of assignable positions M such that a plurality of assignable positions M×N occurs across the plurality of plays N;
displaying, on at least one of the one or more display devices, a plurality of randomly selected symbols in a least some of the assignable positions M for each play of the plurality of plays N;
randomly assigning, via at least one of the one or more processors, the predetermined number of positional game modifiers X across the plurality of plays N to positions in the plurality of assignable positions M×N, the predetermined number of positional game modifiers X being assigned such that each of modifier X1 and modifier X2 is assignable to play N1 or play N2; and
in response to assigning all modifiers of the predetermined number of positional game modifiers X across the plurality of plays N, including modifier X1 being assigned to either of play N1 or play N2 and modifier X2 being assigned to either play N1 or play N2, determining, via at least one of the one or more processors, an outcome for each play of the plurality of plays N taking into account any positional game modifiers X assigned to the assignable positions M.

6. A computer-implemented method for conducting wagering games on a wagering game system, the wagering game system including one or more input devices, one or more display devices, and one or more processors, the method comprising:
receiving a wager in response to an input via at least one of the one or more input devices;
awarding, via at least one of the one or more processors, a progressive award including a plurality of positional game modifiers X, the plurality of positional game modifiers X including modifier X1 and modifier X2;
assigning, via at least one of the one or more processors, the positional game modifiers X to a total number of symbol-bearing positions M×N achieved during a plurality of awarded free plays N including play N1 and N2, each play of the plurality of awarded free plays N having a set of assignable symbol-bearing positions M, the plurality of positional game modifiers X being assigned such that each of modifiers X1 and modifier X2 is assignable to play N1 or play N2;
displaying the plurality of free plays N on at least one of the one or more display devices; and
determining, via at least one of the one or more processors, an outcome for each play of the plurality of awarded free plays N, the outcome being based on any positional game modifiers X assigned to symbol-bearing positions M of each play of the plurality of awarded free plays N, including modifier X1 being assigned to either of play N1 or play N2 and modifier X2 being assigned to either play N1 or play N2.
